	   <tr><td colspan=2>The limit is actually 127, and I'll tell you why.<br>In everquest, the packets you're sending and recieving have 256 bits of information. The first and last bit of info is used as a header and ender, leaving you with 254. Half of 254 = 127.<br><br>It's my guess that item Hitpoints and Mana are using the same 254 bit info to determine the hp and mana amounts on items. That's why the limit is 127.<br>&nbsp;<br>Jarnin Fisheermann<br>58th Evoker<br>&lt;Ring of Cobalt&gt;<br>Rallos Zek</td></tr>
